Vokda's voice catalog spans **25 providers** — a mix of cloud TTS services and open
model ecosystems. Each provider has a stable, machine-friendly `providerId`
(e.g. `elevenlabs`, `aws-polly`) that the SDK, API, and catalog all agree on.
This document is the **single source of truth** for those IDs and the contract
you can rely on when building integrations against them.

> **What this means for you:** you can hard-code `providerId` values in your
> app config, feature flags, or UI logic. We treat a breaking ID change the
> same way we'd treat a breaking API change — it goes through a deprecation
> cycle, a changelog entry, and a migration window.

